# Override Hierarchy

Resolved by `HelixUltimate\Framework\Platform\HTMLOverride::loadTemplate()`:

1. `templates/{template}/overrides/` — template-specific framework override
2. `plugins/system/helixultimate/overrides/` (J5+) or `overrides_legacy/` (J4)
3. Core Joomla extension path

Standard Joomla template overrides also live in:

`templates/shaper_helixultimate/html/{extension}/{view}/{layout}.php`

## Where to put changes

| Goal | Location |
|------|----------|
| This site’s view tweak | `templates/shaper_helixultimate/html/` |
| All Helix templates | `plugins/system/helixultimate/overrides/` |
| J4-only plugin override | `overrides_legacy/` |
| Layout builder partial | Prefer `html/layouts/helixultimate/...` then plugin `layouts/` |

## Rules

- Never patch `components/`, `modules/`, or `plugins/` outside Helix.
- Keep override views thin — business logic stays in framework classes.
- In J4+ layouts, prefer `WebAssetManager` (`registerAndUseScript` / `usePreset`) when adding assets.
- Match existing override structure (copy from core, then edit) so Joomla can find the layout.
